        "width": 100,
        "height": 20
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Remarks. — In case the Deputy authorizes the Clerk's certificate, evidence may be required to show that the Deputy is duly appointed and authorized by law to sign the Clerk's name and use the seal of the Court—therefore it is better to have the Clerk's own dedicated authorization at once, and then rate the trouble and expense of a general authorization certificate respecting the Deputy, which might be required if the papers were authenticated by him instead of the Clerk.",
